                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d149">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">839.415/146a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">White</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-02-10T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >February 10, 1944—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>42. As President Trujillo has taken the initiative, suggested in your 29 of
                    February 7, (according to Ambassador Warren’s 81 of February 9<note n="16"
                        xml:id="d149fn16">Not printed.</note>) you are requested to use your good
                    offices to have President Lescot accept and participate in the border
                    meeting.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
